<%# Run Roster sidebar — Phase 1 in-game info from each session's active save
    slot. Renders one card per session in @run_sessions (typically 4).

    Each session's card is wrapped in a turbo_frame_tag so the
    SoulLinkEmulatorSaveSlot model's after_*_commit broadcast can replace
    just that frame's contents when parsed_* fields update — without
    reloading the whole emulator page (which would tear down the running
    emulator iframe).

    The YOU badge + 4px-border are applied client-side by the
    `roster-you-marker` Stimulus controller, which walks
    [data-discord-user-id] cards on connect + on each
    turbo:before-stream-render. This keeps current_user_id out of the
    model callback (broadcast renders run without controller context)
    and the marker re-applies across frame replacements. %>

<div data-controller="roster-you-marker"
     data-roster-you-marker-current-user-id-value="<%= current_user_id %>">
  <div class="gb-card" style="padding: 8px 10px; margin-bottom: 8px;">
    <div style="font-size: 11px; color: var(--d1); letter-spacing: 0.1em;">RUN ROSTER</div>
  </div>

  <% @run_sessions.each do |s| %>
    <%= turbo_frame_tag "emulator_roster_session_#{s.id}" do %>
      <%= render "emulator/run_sidebar_card", s: s %>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
</div>
